definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  histone H4 N6-acetyl-L-lysine (position 16) + H2O -eq- histone H4 L-lysine (position 16) + acetate. This reaction requires the presence of NAD, and represents the removal of an acetyl group from lysine at position 16 of the histone H4 protein.

Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + histone H4 L-lysine (position 16) -eq- CoA + histone H4 N6-acetyl-L-lysine (position 16). This reaction represents the addition of an acetyl group to the lysine at position 16 of histone H4.

Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + histone H3 L-lysine (position 9) -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + histone H3 N6-methyl-L-lysine (position 9). This reaction is the addition of a methyl group onto lysine at position 9 of the histone H3 protein.

Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + histone H3 L-lysine (position 36) -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + histone H3 N6-methyl-L-lysine (position 36). This reaction is the addition of a methyl group onto lysine at position 36 of the histone H3 protein.

Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + histone H3 L-lysine (position 27) -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + histone H3 N6-methyl-L-lysine (position 27). This reaction is the addition of a methyl group onto lysine at position 27 of the histone H3 protein.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with TAP protein, transporter associated with antigen processing protein. TAP protein is a heterodimeric peptide transporter consisting of the subunits TAP1 and TAP2.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the TAP1 subunit of TAP (transporter associated with antigen processing) protein.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the TAP2 subunit of TAP (transporter associated with antigen processing) protein.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with tapasin, a member of the MHC class I loading complex which bridges the TAP peptide transporter to class I molecules.
Catalysis of the transfer of N-acetylglucosamine (GlcNAc) in a beta-1,3 linkage to the mannose(beta-1,4)Glc disaccharide core of glycolipids.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a nonidentical protein to form a heterodimer.
The formation of a protein dimer, a macromolecular structure consists of two noncovalently associated identical or nonidentical subunits.
Catalysis of the transfer, in a beta 1,3 linkage, of D-glucuronic acid (GlcUA) from UDP-D-glucuronic acid to N-acetyllactosamine (galactosyl beta-1,4-N-acetylglucosamine).
Catalysis of the transfer, in a beta 1,3 linkage, of D-glucuronic acid (GlcUA) from UDP-GlcUA to asioloorosomucoid.

Catalysis of the transfer, in a beta 1,3 linkage, of D-glucuronic acid (GlcUA) from UDP-GlcUA to the disaccharide galactosyl beta-1,3 N-acetylgalactosamine, a common component of glycoproteins and glycolipids.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + an N-hydroxyarylamine -eq- CoA + an N-acetoxyarylamine.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on X-H and Y-H to form an X-Y bond

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which X-H and Y-H form X-Y.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on X-H and Y-H to form an X-Y bond, with oxygen as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which X-H and Y-H form X-Y and the acceptor is oxygen.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on hydrogen as donor, with a quinone or similar compound as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen acts as an electron donor and reduces quinone or similar compound.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on hydrogen as donor, with other known acceptors

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen reduces a known acceptor other than a cytochrome, an iron-sulfur protein, NAD, NADP, or a quinone or similar compound.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, with NAD(P)H as one donor, and the other dehydrogenated

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which hydrogen or electrons are transferred from NADH or NADPH and one other donor, and the latter donor is dehydrogenated.

label.value: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-NH group of donors, flavin as acceptor

definition.value: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH-NH group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a flavin.
